### 2. Backend — SSE Endpoint + notifyHandler push integration

#### [NEW] `backend/src/modules/notifications/sse.js`
A singleton **SSE connection registry** that holds a `Map<userId, Set<SSEResponse>>`. Exported functions:
- `registerClient(userId, res)` — adds SSE response to the map
- `removeClient(userId, res)` — removes on disconnect
- `pushToUser(userId, event, data)` — writes an SSE frame to all open tabs for a user
- `pushToAll(event, data)` — broadcasts to all connected clients

#### [MODIFY] [notifications.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/Ashmi/OneDrive/Desktop/Crime-Diaries/backend/src/modules/notifications/notifications.routes.js)
Add a new `GET /stream` route:
```
router.get('/stream', authenticate, (req, res) => {
  res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');
  res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');
  res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');
  res.flushHeaders();
  registerClient(req.user.id, res);
  // heartbeat every 30s to keep connection alive
  const hb = setInterval(() => res.write(':heartbeat\n\n'), 30000);
  req.on('close', () => { clearInterval(hb); removeClient(req.user.id, res); });
});
```

#### [MODIFY] [notifyHandler.js](file:///c:/Users/Ashmi/OneDrive/Desktop/Crime-Diaries/backend/src/events/handlers/notifyHandler.js)
After each `db('notifications').insert(...)`, call `pushToUser(userId, 'notification', { ...notificationRow })` so the frontend gets an instant push.

